<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.PT4"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="part" searchtype="LEGISLATION PART" subdoc="false" toc-caption="PART 4 ATTACHMENT OF INSURANCE MONEYS [s 6]">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading><desig searchtype="PART-NUM"><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.PT4" type="ext"/>PART 4</designum></desig><title searchtype="PART-TITLE">ATTACHMENT OF INSURANCE MONEYS [s 6]</title></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[360,150] s 6 Amount of liability to be charge on insurance moneys payable against that liability">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6" type="ext"/>[360,150]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">Amount of liability to be charge on insurance moneys payable against that liability</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>6</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>If any person (hereinafter in this Part referred to as the insured) has, whether before or after the commencement of this Act, entered into a contract of insurance by which the person is indemnified against liability to pay any damages or compensation, the amount of the person's liability shall on the happening of the event giving rise to the claim for damages or compensation, and notwithstanding that the amount of such liability may not then have been determined, be a charge on all insurance moneys that are or may become payable in respect of that liability.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subs (1)  am Act 30 of 1996  sÂ 3 and Sch 3]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>If, on the happening of the event giving rise to any claim for damages or compensation as aforesaid, the insured (being a corporation) is being wound up, or if any subsequent winding-up of the insured (being a corporation) is deemed to have commenced not later than the happening of that event, the provisions of 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.1" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">subsection (1)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 shall apply notwithstanding the winding-up.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.3" type="ext"/>(3)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Every charge created by this section shall have priority over all other charges affecting the said insurance moneys, and where the same insurance moneys are subject to two or more charges by virtue of this Part those charges shall have priority between themselves in the order of the dates of the events out of which the liability arose, or, if such charges arise out of events happening on the same date, they shall rank equally between themselves.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.4"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.4" type="ext"/>(4)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Every such charge as aforesaid shall be enforceable by way of an action against the insurer in the same way and in the same court as if the action were an action to recover damages or compensation from the insured; and in respect of any such action and of the judgment given therein the parties shall, to the extent of the charge, have the same rights and liabilities, and the court shall have the same powers, as if the action were against the insured:  Provided that, except where the provisions of 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.2" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">subsection (2)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 apply, no such action shall be commenced in any court except with the leave of that court. Leave shall not be granted in any case where the court is satisfied that the insurer is entitled under the terms of the contract of insurance to disclaim liability, and that any proceedings, including arbitration proceedings, necessary to establish that the insurer is so entitled to disclaim, have been taken.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.5"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.5" type="ext"/>(5)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Such an action may be brought although judgment has been already recovered against the insured for damages or compensation in respect of the same matter.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.6"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.6" type="ext"/>(6)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Any payment made by an insurer under the contract of insurance without actual notice of the existence of any such charge shall to the extent of that payment be a valid discharge to the insurer, notwithstanding anything in this Part contained.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.7"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.7" type="ext"/>(7)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>No insurer shall be liable under this Part for any greater sum than that fixed by the contract of insurance between the insurer and the insured.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subs (7)  am Act 30 of 1996  sÂ 3 and Sch 3]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.8"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.8" type="ext"/>(8)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Nothing in this section shall affect the operation of any of the provisions of the 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="OTH.WCN" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID" status="unval">Workers' Compensation Act 1987</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 , or the 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="OTH.MOT" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID" status="unval">Motor Vehicles (Third Party Insurance) Act 1942</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 .</text></p>
<glp:note>
<p><text><ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF" type="legref"><ci:content>cf NZ Act 31 of 1936 sÂ 9</ci:content></ci:cite></text></p></glp:note><leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subs (8)  am Act 79 of 1987  sÂ 3 and Sch 1]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.9"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.9" type="ext"/>(9)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Despite subsection (8), this section applies in relation to a policy of workers compensation insurance entered into by an employer (whether entered into before or after the commencement of this subsection), where the employer:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.9..A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.9..A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>being a natural person, has died, or is permanently resident outside the Commonwealth and its Territories, or cannot after due inquiry and search be found, or</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.9..B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.9..B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>being a corporation (other than a company that has commenced to be wound up), has ceased to exist, or</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.9..C"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.9..C" type="ext"/>(c)</lilabel>
<p><text>being a company, corporation, society, association or other body (other than a company that has commenced to be wound up), was at the time when it commenced to employ workers to which the policy relates incorporated outside the Commonwealth and its Territories and registered as a foreign company under the laws of any State or Territory and is not so registered under any such law, or</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.9..D"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.9..D" type="ext"/>(d)</lilabel>
<p><text>being a company, is in the course of being wound up.</text></p>
</li>
</l><leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subs (9)  insrt Act 130 of 1998  sÂ 3 and Sch 3]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:bodytext>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTES"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTES</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.360150-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[360,150.5] Liability to pay damages or compensation"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.360150-5" type="ext"/>[360,150.5] </edpnum><title>Liability to pay damages or compensation</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>The section applies where the insurance contract includes an indemnity against liability to contribute as a tortfeasor liable for the same damage: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1981"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000370" spanref="cr000370-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:page num="400"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">National Mutual Fire Insurance Co Ltd v Commonwealth</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000370-001">[1981] 1Â NSWLR 400</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> .</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.360150-10" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[360,150.10] Limitation period">
<glp:note><blockquote><hrule/>
<p>
<text><inlineobject attachment="web-server" filename="leg1.gif" type="image"/> Legislation cited in [360,150.10] below. LawNow subscribers click through for daily updates and historical versions.</text><text>Â </text>
<text>(NSW) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005Y" refpt="NSW_ACT_1946-33" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Law Reform (Miscellaneous Provisions) Act 1946</remotelink> sÂ 6(4).</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
<text>(NSW) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005Y" refpt="NSW_ACT_1969-31" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Limitation Act 1969</remotelink>.</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
</p></blockquote></glp:note><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.360150-10" type="ext"/>[360,150.10] </edpnum><title>Limitation period</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text><ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6.4" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Section 6(4)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 stipulates that the charge is enforceable in an action against the insurer &#x201c;as if the action were an action to recover damages or compensation from the insured&#x201d;. Consequently, if proceedings are taken against the insured within time, including within the period of any extension granted under the 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.LAN" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Limitation Act 1969</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 , an insurer cannot raise a limitation defence in proceedings brought to enforce the charge under the present section. Conversely, if the limitation period expires before any proceedings have been brought against either the insured or the insurer, the expiry of the period will bar any subsequent claim against the insurer: In <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1999"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000371" spanref="cr000371-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="46"/><ci:page num="32"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000372" spanref="cr000372-002"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC9900196"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Kinzett v McCourt</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000371-001">(1999) 46 NSWLR 32</ci:span>; [1999] NSWCAÂ 7; <ci:span spanid="cr000372-002"> BC9900196</ci:span></citefragment>Â <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="293473" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> overruling <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1991"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000373" spanref="cr000373-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="25"/><ci:page num="422"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000374" spanref="cr000374-002" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="ANZInsCas"/><ci:volume num="7"/><ci:page num="61[ndash ]095"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Grimson v Aviation &amp; General (Underwriting) Agents Pty Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000373-001">(1991) 25 NSWLR 422</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000374-002" status="unval">7 ANZ Ins CasÂ Â¶61&#x2013;095</ci:span></citefragment>Â <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="35164" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> and <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1993"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000375" spanref="cr000375-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="31"/><ci:page num="469"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000376" spanref="cr000376-002"><ci:reporter value="ACSR"/><ci:volume num="11"/><ci:page num="406"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">New South Wales Medical Defence Union Ltd v Crawford</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000375-001">(1993) 31 NSWLR 469</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000376-002">11 ACSR 406</ci:span></citefragment>Â <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="46887" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> .</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.360150-15" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[360,150.15] Leave"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.360150-15" type="ext"/>[360,150.15] </edpnum><title>Leave</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>Leave will not be granted if there is an available common law defendant to the principal claim &#x2014; unless there is a basis to doubt the likelihood of actual recovery from the insured: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000377" spanref="cr000377-001"><ci:reporter value="NZLR"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1971"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="240"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000377" spanref="cr000377-002"><ci:pinpoint num="243" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Campbell v Mutual Life and Citizens Fire and General Insurance Co (NZ) Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000377-001">[1971] NZLR 240</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000377-002">at 243</ci:span></citefragment>Â <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="31834" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> ; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1987"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000378" spanref="cr000378-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="11"/><ci:page num="715"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000378" spanref="cr000378-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="725" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Oswald v Bailey</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000378-001">(1987) 11 NSWLR 715</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000378-002" status="unval">at 725</ci:span></citefragment>Â <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="11602" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> . A claimant's disinclination to bring proceedings against the insured, eg, because of the personal or business relationship between them, is not a proper basis for granting leave: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1981"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000379" spanref="cr000379-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:page num="400"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">National Mutual Fire Insurance Co Ltd v Commonwealth</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000379-001">[1981] 1Â NSWLR 400</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> .</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.360150-20" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[360,150.20] Notional charge"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.360150-20" type="ext"/>[360,150.20] </edpnum><title>Notional charge</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>The charge provided for by the section attaches when the event giving rise to the claim for damages occurs. The subject matter of the charge must also be determined at that time: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1987"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000380" spanref="cr000380-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="11"/><ci:page num="715"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Oswald v Bailey</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000380-001">(1987) 11 NSWLR 715</ci:span></citefragment>Â <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="11602" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> . Consequently, there are conflicting authorities as to whether the section applies to &#x201c;claims made and notified&#x201d; contracts of insurance where the event giving rise to the claim for damages occurs before the period of the policy. The section was held not to apply in <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1993"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000381" spanref="cr000381-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="ANZInsCas"/><ci:volume num="7"/><ci:page num="61180"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">NP Manettas v Underwriters at Lloyds</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000381-001" status="unval">(1993) 7Â ANZ Ins CasÂ Â¶61&#x2013;180</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> ; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000382" spanref="cr000382-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC9804895"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Schipp v Cameron</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000382-001" status="unval"> (NSWSC, Einstein J, 9Â July 1998, unreported, BC9804895)</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> . The contrary view was taken, and the section applied, in <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1995"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000383" spanref="cr000383-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="ACLC"/><ci:volume num="13"/><ci:page num="1781"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Jones v Mortgage Acceptance Nominees Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000383-001" status="unval">(1995) 13 ACLC 1781</ci:span></citefragment>Â <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="120170" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> ; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1996"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000384" spanref="cr000384-001"><ci:reporter value="ALR"/><ci:volume num="138"/><ci:page num="409"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000385" spanref="cr000385-002" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="ANZInsCas"/><ci:volume num="9"/><ci:page num="61[ndash ]335"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">National Mutual Property Services (Aust) Pty Ltd v Citibank Savings Ltd (No 4)</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000384-001">(1996) 138 ALR 409</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000385-002" status="unval">9 ANZ Ins CasÂ Â¶61&#x2013;335</ci:span></citefragment>Â <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="171871" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> ; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1997"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000386" spanref="cr000386-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="FCR"/><ci:volume num="73"/><ci:page num="379"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000387" spanref="cr000387-002"><ci:reporter value="ALR"/><ci:volume num="154"/><ci:page num="229"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">FAI General Insurance Co Ltd v McSweeeney</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000386-001" status="unval">(1997) 73 FCR 379</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000387-002">154 ALR 229</ci:span></citefragment>Â <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="220269" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> .</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.360150-25" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[360,150.25] Insurer entitled to deny liability">
<glp:note><blockquote><hrule/>
<p>
<text><inlineobject attachment="web-server" filename="leg1.gif" type="image"/> Legislation cited in [360,150.25] below. LawNow subscribers click through for daily updates and historical versions.</text><text>Â </text>
<text>(NSW) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005Y" refpt="NSW_ACT_1946-33" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Law Reform (Miscellaneous Provisions) Act 1946</remotelink> sÂ 6.</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
</p></blockquote></glp:note><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.360150-25" type="ext"/>[360,150.25] </edpnum><title>Insurer entitled to deny liability</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text><ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.LRMP.S6" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Section 6</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 is not intended to enlarge the insurer's liability. Accordingly, when the insurer is entitled to decline liability, there is no right to a charge nor an action against the insurer: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1991"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000388" spanref="cr000388-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="25"/><ci:page num="422"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000389" spanref="cr000389-002" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="ANZInsCas"/><ci:volume num="7"/><ci:page num="61[ndash ]095"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Grimson v Aviation &amp; General (Underwriting) Agents Pty Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000388-001">(1991) 25 NSWLR 422</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000389-002" status="unval">7 ANZ Ins CasÂ Â¶61&#x2013;095</ci:span></citefragment>Â <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="35164" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> ; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1993"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000390" spanref="cr000390-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="31"/><ci:page num="538"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000391" spanref="cr000391-002" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="ANZInsCas"/><ci:volume num="7"/><ci:page num="61[ndash ]194"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">McMillan v Mannix</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000390-001">(1993) 31 NSWLR 538</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000391-002" status="unval">7 ANZ Ins CasÂ Â¶61&#x2013;194</ci:span></citefragment>Â <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="50060" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> . Similarly, leave should be refused if the primary limitation period against the insured has expired: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1999"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000392" spanref="cr000392-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="46"/><ci:page num="32"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000393" spanref="cr000393-002"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC9900196"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Kinzett v McCourt</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000392-001">(1999) 46 NSWLR 32</ci:span>; [1999] NSWCA 7; <ci:span spanid="cr000393-002"> BC9900196</ci:span></citefragment>Â <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="293473" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> .</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.360150-30" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[360,150.30] Time when the charge arises"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.360150-30" type="ext"/>[360,150.30] </edpnum><title>Time when the charge arises</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>The charge arises on the happening of the event that gives rise to, in the sense of completing, the cause of action of the third party against the insured. It does not refer to the act or omission constituting the breach of the duty owed to the third party: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000394" spanref="cr000394-001"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC9302088"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000394" spanref="cr000394-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="84" targettype="para"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Capita Financial Group Ltd v Triden Properties Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000394-001"> (NSWSC, Cole J, 6Â September 1993, unreported, BC9302088)</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000394-002" status="unval">at [84]</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> ; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1996"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000395" spanref="cr000395-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="BCL"/><ci:volume num="12"/><ci:page num="402"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000396" spanref="cr000396-002"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC9501836"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Triden Properties Ltd v Capita Financial Group Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000395-001" status="unval">(1996) 12 BCL 402</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000396-002"> BC9501836</ci:span></citefragment>Â <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="128771" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite> .</text></p>
</bodytext>
